          Because {name} does not levy a state income tax, the sales tax takes on heightened importance as a revenue source for funding state government operations. Without income tax revenue, {name} depends more heavily on sales tax collections, property taxes, and other fees to finance public services. The sales tax rate of {formatPercent(salesTax.stateRate * 100)} at the state level, combined with local additions that bring the average to {formatPercent(salesTax.avgCombinedRate * 100)}, generates a substantial portion of the revenue needed to operate state agencies, fund transportation projects, and support other government functions. For residents, this means that while they benefit from not paying state income tax on their wages, they bear a proportionally higher burden through sales tax on their purchases. To understand how this trade-off affects your finances, use our <a href={`/paycheck-calculator/${slug}/`} class="text-navy-600 hover:text-navy-700 dark:text-navy-400 dark:hover:text-navy-300">{name} paycheck calculator</a> to see your take-home pay without state income tax withholding.
        </p>
