      {!isNoTax && !isNoSalesTax && salesTax && (
        <p>
          In {name}, sales tax works alongside the state income tax and property taxes to form a three-legged tax system that collectively funds government operations at both the state and local levels. The income tax captures a portion of each resident's earnings, the sales tax captures a portion of each resident's spending, and property taxes capture a portion of each resident's real estate wealth. Together, these three tax types create a diversified revenue base that helps {name} maintain stable funding for public services even when one revenue source fluctuates due to economic conditions. For residents, this means that the total tax burden must be evaluated across all three dimensions to get an accurate picture of the cost of living in {name}. You can explore your full income tax obligation using our <a href={`/paycheck-calculator/${slug}/`} class="text-navy-600 hover:text-navy-700 dark:text-navy-400 dark:hover:text-navy-300">{name} paycheck calculator</a>, and you can estimate your property tax costs with our <a href={`/property-tax-calculator/${slug}/`} class="text-navy-600 hover:text-navy-700 dark:text-navy-400 dark:hover:text-navy-300">{name} property tax calculator</a>.
