      {isNoSalesTax && (
        <p>
          The absence of a sales tax in {name} means that the state's tax burden falls on fewer types of taxes, creating a different tax profile than most other states. Whether through higher income taxes, higher property taxes, or alternative taxes on businesses, {name} has found ways to fund government operations without relying on a broad-based consumption tax. This creates a distinct set of advantages and trade-offs that residents should evaluate based on their personal financial circumstances. High-income earners who spend relatively little of their income may benefit from the lack of a sales tax, while residents with lower incomes but significant property holdings may feel the impact of higher property taxes more acutely. Exploring these trade-offs using our <a href={`/property-tax-calculator/${slug}/`} class="text-navy-600 hover:text-navy-700 dark:text-navy-400 dark:hover:text-navy-300">{name} property tax calculator</a> and <a href={`/paycheck-calculator/${slug}/`} class="text-navy-600 hover:text-navy-700 dark:text-navy-400 dark:hover:text-navy-300">{name} paycheck calculator</a> can help you understand your full tax picture.
